    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 125,
    "last_activity_date" : 1752704156,
    "last_edit_date" : 1752704156,
    "creation_date" : 1516695424,
    "answer_id" : 48396996,
    "question_id" : 138511,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Since Java 9.0 JDWP supports only local connections by default.\n<a href=\"https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase/9-all-relnotes.html#JDK-8041435\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/javase/9-all-relnotes.html#JDK-8041435</a></p>\n<p>For remote debugging one should run program with <code>*:</code> in address:</p>\n<pre><code>-agentlib:jdwp=transport=dt_socket,server=y,suspend=n,address=*:8000\n</code></pre>\n<p><strong>Caution</strong>: this allows anyone who can reach the specified port (here 8000) on any of the machine's IP addresses to control the process, which is exactly why it's no longer the default.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7881563,
      "reputation" : 101,
      "user_id" : 9573426,
      "user_type" : "registered",
